300
00:32:11,080 --> 00:32:12,960
I'm Peter.

301
00:32:13,040 --> 00:32:14,480
James isn't here today.

302
00:32:18,280 --> 00:32:19,520
Is this funny?

303
00:32:20,760 --> 00:32:21,920
Who's laughing?

304
00:32:22,880 --> 00:32:24,840
Laugh and I'll have
you come up here to sing.

305
00:32:24,920 --> 00:32:27,280
I'm not as nice as James.

306
00:32:30,280 --> 00:32:32,600
Hey, why isn't anyone laughing?

307
00:32:33,880 --> 00:32:34,920
All right then.

308
00:32:35,520 --> 00:32:38,600
Well then, nice, old James is back.

309
00:32:39,560 --> 00:32:42,600
I've been wearing this mask for so long…

310
00:32:42,680 --> 00:32:45,080
that I've forgotten what I look like.

311
00:32:46,080 --> 00:32:47,280
What about you?

312
00:32:47,920 --> 00:32:50,280
Do you wear masks too?

313
00:32:50,800 --> 00:32:55,000
Especially when you've been hurt.

314
00:32:55,920 --> 00:32:57,760
Do you find yourself thinking…

315
00:32:58,280 --> 00:32:59,880
that life is full of pain?

316
00:33:01,440 --> 00:33:03,600
Whether you like it or not,

317
00:33:03,680 --> 00:33:06,160
you're always hurting.

318
00:33:06,240 --> 00:33:08,120
"I just want to be happy.

319
00:33:08,200 --> 00:33:09,360
I don't want to hurt anymore."

320
00:33:09,440 --> 00:33:11,440
But this is impossible,

321
00:33:11,960 --> 00:33:15,880
because joy and pain go hand-in-hand.

322
00:33:17,120 --> 00:33:20,200
Many people don't know
how to deal with their pain,

323
00:33:20,280 --> 00:33:22,000
so they put on masks,

324
00:33:22,800 --> 00:33:25,960
because they're afraid
of getting hurt again.

325
00:33:27,160 --> 00:33:28,800
You know what's worse?

326
00:33:28,880 --> 00:33:33,240
Some people use vices to numb themselves.

327
00:33:34,040 --> 00:33:36,400
Like alcohol, for example,

328
00:33:37,200 --> 00:33:38,200
or drugs,

329
00:33:38,960 --> 00:33:40,360
medications,

330
00:33:40,440 --> 00:33:42,160
smut

331
00:33:42,240 --> 00:33:44,760
or violent games.

332
00:33:51,960 --> 00:33:56,520
We allow escapism, hatred and pain…

333
00:33:56,600 --> 00:33:59,520
to eat away at our weak hearts.

334
00:33:59,600 --> 00:34:00,440
What then?

335
00:34:01,040 --> 00:34:02,280
Let God…

336
00:34:02,800 --> 00:34:05,480
heal your pain.

337
00:34:07,120 --> 00:34:08,159
Come on.

338
00:34:08,920 --> 00:34:12,120
Let's turn
to Proverbs chapter 17, verse 22,

339
00:34:12,199 --> 00:34:13,800
and read this aloud together.

340
00:34:18,159 --> 00:34:20,520
"A joyful heart is good medicine,

341
00:34:21,560 --> 00:34:25,280
but a crushed spirit dries up the bones."

342
00:34:30,120 --> 00:34:31,639
Why did you leave halfway?

343
00:34:32,960 --> 00:34:34,400
There's no twist to it at all.

344
00:34:35,560 --> 00:34:37,480
Maybe you're just not used to this yet.

345
00:34:37,560 --> 00:34:39,239
Maybe it'll be fine
after a few more sessions.

346
00:34:40,199 --> 00:34:41,360
How many more?

347
00:34:42,040 --> 00:34:43,679
This is for you.

348
00:34:43,760 --> 00:34:46,440
Our new friends are all stars to us.

349
00:34:46,520 --> 00:34:49,760
Next time, if you don't leave
during the sermon,

350
00:34:49,840 --> 00:34:51,920
we'll give you two stars.

351
00:34:53,400 --> 00:34:54,800
There won't be a next time.

352
00:34:55,880 --> 00:34:57,360
Shanwen.

353
00:34:59,560 --> 00:35:00,520
Here you go.

354
00:35:11,800 --> 00:35:13,120
- God bless you.
- Thank you.

355
00:35:13,640 --> 00:35:15,200
- God bless you.
- Thank you.

356
00:35:16,760 --> 00:35:17,600
See you.

357
00:35:18,800 --> 00:35:21,000
Don't be so long-winded next time, Pastor.

358
00:35:21,080 --> 00:35:22,080
Keep it short.

359
00:35:22,160 --> 00:35:23,240
Everyone's hungry.

360
00:35:24,080 --> 00:35:25,400
Don't be rude.

361
00:35:26,200 --> 00:35:27,720
Were you paying attention?

362
00:35:27,800 --> 00:35:29,720
I saw you on your phone.

363
00:35:29,800 --> 00:35:32,600
I was just verifying what you said.

364
00:35:32,680 --> 00:35:35,360
Cindy, you're a vice leader.

365
00:35:35,440 --> 00:35:36,800
You have to set a good example

366
00:35:36,880 --> 00:35:38,360
because many of the lambs look up to you.

367
00:35:38,440 --> 00:35:40,280
More of them look up to Tingting,

368
00:35:40,360 --> 00:35:43,000
and she's on her phone more than I am.

369
00:35:43,080 --> 00:35:43,960
Bye, Pastor.

370
00:35:45,880 --> 00:35:47,480
I'll talk some sense into her.

371
00:35:47,560 --> 00:35:49,040
- All right. God bless you.
- Pastor.

372
00:35:49,120 --> 00:35:49,960
Bye.

373
00:35:58,600 --> 00:35:59,800
Zhang Tingting.

374
00:36:00,480 --> 00:36:02,160
Someone really stood out earlier,

375
00:36:02,680 --> 00:36:04,240
running out while I was preaching.

376
00:36:04,320 --> 00:36:05,880
That wasn't very pious of you.

377
00:36:06,600 --> 00:36:09,040
I worked so hard to get my classmate here,

378
00:36:09,120 --> 00:36:12,120
so I had to ask him
why he left so suddenly.

379
00:36:12,200 --> 00:36:13,920
You could have texted him.

380
00:36:14,000 --> 00:36:16,840
You ran out in your heels,
clicking and clacking.

381
00:36:16,920 --> 00:36:18,080
Everyone was looking at you.

382
00:36:18,600 --> 00:36:19,560
Dad.

383
00:36:19,640 --> 00:36:21,240
Don't you always tell me…

384
00:36:21,320 --> 00:36:23,480
that our new friends are stars?

385
00:36:23,560 --> 00:36:25,280
If the US president was here,

386
00:36:25,360 --> 00:36:27,800
would you run after him,
or would you text him?

387
00:36:28,600 --> 00:36:29,920
The US president, huh?

388
00:36:30,000 --> 00:36:31,520
All right, I surrender.

389
00:36:33,240 --> 00:36:34,920
Don't forget that you're my daughter.

390
00:36:35,000 --> 00:36:36,560
You have to set a good example.

391
00:36:37,080 --> 00:36:38,800
Don't put me in a difficult position.

392
00:36:39,880 --> 00:36:41,880
Have I, Pastor Zhang?

393
00:36:43,080 --> 00:36:45,680
Don't wear
such eye-catching heels next time.

394
00:36:50,120 --> 00:36:51,800
It's tough being a daughter,

395
00:36:51,880 --> 00:36:54,040
but it's even worse
being a pastor's daughter.

396
00:36:55,120 --> 00:36:58,200
The real struggle
is raising such a stubborn daughter.

397
00:36:58,280 --> 00:37:01,240
Yeah. My heart breaks for you.

398
00:37:01,320 --> 00:37:02,960
One minute, you wear a father's mask.

399
00:37:03,040 --> 00:37:04,600
The next, you wear a mother's mask.

400
00:37:06,920 --> 00:37:09,000
Why don't I treat you to a meal, Dad?

401
00:37:10,840 --> 00:37:13,320
You make it sound so nice,
but I'm still the one paying.

402
00:37:13,400 --> 00:37:15,720
I guess nothing comes for free.

403
00:37:15,800 --> 00:37:16,880
Is that a no?

404
00:37:17,960 --> 00:37:19,160
That's fine with me.

405
00:37:20,960 --> 00:37:22,280
Did I say no?

406
00:37:22,360 --> 00:37:23,560
I'm in.

407
00:37:23,640 --> 00:37:24,760
What are we having?

408
00:37:25,280 --> 00:37:26,720
What I like!

409
00:38:13,720 --> 00:38:15,720
Such is reality.

410
00:38:16,720 --> 00:38:19,480
It's easy to talk
about staging a comeback,

411
00:38:20,000 --> 00:38:22,200
but even my husband won't support me.

412
00:38:23,440 --> 00:38:27,120
Your husband… has no real power.

413
00:38:30,960 --> 00:38:32,520
These days, to run an exhibition,

414
00:38:33,040 --> 00:38:34,440
you need gimmicks.

415
00:38:36,000 --> 00:38:38,720
I'm your guy for that.

416
00:38:40,800 --> 00:38:41,920
Will you help me?

417
00:39:15,120 --> 00:39:17,080
<i>Many people have forgotten about you.</i>

418
00:39:18,520 --> 00:39:19,840
<i>But don't worry.</i>

419
00:39:20,720 --> 00:39:23,440
<i>I'll make sure you'll never be forgotten.</i>

420
00:39:24,240 --> 00:39:26,120
<i>I'll lure your killer out…</i>

421
00:39:27,160 --> 00:39:28,520
<i>and take revenge for you.</i>

422
00:41:33,880 --> 00:41:35,880
Mrs. Shaw, since you're from Hong Kong,

423
00:41:35,960 --> 00:41:38,880
